267
00:17:39,459 --> 00:17:43,730
Even if the sky collapses, we must fill our stomachs.

268
00:17:49,730 --> 00:17:52,049
When your dad called me

269
00:17:52,050 --> 00:17:53,909
and told me he was sending you over,

270
00:17:53,909 --> 00:17:58,000
I already planned to spank you until you went home.

271
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,159
His dad said I know nothing about raising children.

272
00:18:00,159 --> 00:18:01,500
Spanking children no longer works.

273
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:04,230
We should wait for him to become sensible.

274
00:18:04,239 --> 00:18:05,349
That's right.

275
00:18:05,349 --> 00:18:10,330
Granny, there's an International Spank Out Day.

276
00:18:10,330 --> 00:18:12,350
What day?

277
00:18:12,350 --> 00:18:14,949
It's similar to Children's Day.

278
00:18:14,949 --> 00:18:18,000
On that day, parents can't spank their children.

279
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,699
That's not today, right?

280
00:18:19,699 --> 00:18:22,850
I can spank him on any other day, can't I?

281
00:18:23,700 --> 00:18:25,949
Why can't I spank him?

282
00:18:25,949 --> 00:18:28,389
He needs a spanking.

283
00:18:28,389 --> 00:18:31,019
He's spoiled and does as he pleases.

284
00:18:31,019 --> 00:18:34,120
I can't spank him when he doesn't go to school.

285
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:37,149
In the end, he ran away from home.

286
00:18:37,149 --> 00:18:40,949
If I don't spank him, he'll become a thief

287
00:18:40,949 --> 00:18:42,829
just like Xie Qiang.

288
00:18:42,829 --> 00:18:44,430
Granny!

289
00:18:49,220 --> 00:18:51,200
Fine, I'll stop.

290
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,720
Eat up.

291
00:18:58,260 --> 00:19:01,259
Thank you, Granny.

292
00:19:05,010 --> 00:19:07,640
Granny, I'll return to work.

293
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:10,090
Why should a student be working?

294
00:19:10,670 --> 00:19:12,109
Come home with me later.

295
00:19:12,109 --> 00:19:14,730
I'll ask your dad to pick you up.

296
00:19:14,730 --> 00:19:16,109
Granny.

297
00:19:16,109 --> 00:19:20,219
I have to work two more days this week to receive my salary.

298
00:19:25,010 --> 00:19:27,330
Go and work.

299
00:19:27,330 --> 00:19:29,620
Make sure you comb your hair first.

300
00:19:34,570 --> 00:19:36,530
I'm off, Granny.

301
00:19:39,300 --> 00:19:41,800
Why are you letting him work?

302
00:19:42,460 --> 00:19:44,549
He earns a weekly salary here.

303
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:46,539
He's worked for five days, and two days more isn't much.

304
00:19:46,539 --> 00:19:48,289
Let him finish it.

305
00:19:48,289 --> 00:19:50,979
You should've told me where he was.

306
00:19:50,979 --> 00:19:52,529
I know you like the back of my hand.

307
00:19:52,529 --> 00:19:57,229
If I told you, you would've charged here and ruined my plans.

308
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:00,720
When did you find out about his whereabouts?

309
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:02,860
I found out the moment he entered this place.

310
00:20:05,530 --> 00:20:07,500
I have an informant.

311
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:09,429
<i>Welcome!</i>

312
00:20:09,429 --> 00:20:11,559
<i>You have to channel your breath into it.</i>

313
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:13,389
<i>Welcome!</i>

314
00:20:13,389 --> 00:20:14,829
<i>You have to pay attention to the rhythm.</i>

315
00:20:14,829 --> 00:20:16,499
<i>Welcome!</i>

316
00:20:16,499 --> 00:20:19,390
<i>Be enthusiastic and brave!</i>

317
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:26,119
♪ <i>Be brave</i> ♪

318
00:20:26,119 --> 00:20:29,299
♪ <i>This darkness</i> ♪

319
00:20:29,299 --> 00:20:35,399
♪ <i>is nothing but a misunderstanding</i> ♪

320
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:41,650
♪ <i>The twists and turns in life</i> ♪

321
00:20:44,730 --> 00:20:46,690
<i>Brother Liang, I need the washroom.</i>

322
00:20:46,690 --> 00:20:49,320
<i>- I have a stomach ache.
- Go on.</i>

323
00:20:58,190 --> 00:20:59,890
<i>Brother?</i>

324
00:20:59,890 --> 00:21:01,550
<i>Xie—</i>

325
00:21:06,060 --> 00:21:07,969
<i>So, you've only picked up bad habits like smoking and drinking?</i>

326
00:21:07,970 --> 00:21:09,759
<i>I-I didn't. I seldom do it.</i>

327
00:21:09,759 --> 00:21:11,380
<i>Seldom?</i>

328
00:21:11,380 --> 00:21:13,670
<i>I'll quit smoking.</i>

329
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:15,909
<i>Why are you here?</i>

330
00:21:15,909 --> 00:21:18,140
<i>Didn't your mom take you to Ruili?</i>

331
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:20,019
<i>My mom's place is too crowded.</i>

332
00:21:20,019 --> 00:21:22,430
<i>I might as well return here and work.</i>

333
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:28,629
<i>Why did A'Yuan go to you?</i>

334
00:21:28,629 --> 00:21:31,979
<i>We often play video games with Brother Xia Xia.</i>

335
00:21:31,979 --> 00:21:34,979
<i>He came to me out of the blue and asked for a job.</i>

336
00:21:34,979 --> 00:21:36,850
<i>So, you've gathered to fool around</i>

337
00:21:36,850 --> 00:21:39,300
<i>and sing hand in hand?</i>

338
00:21:40,390 --> 00:21:42,109
<i>Brother, why don't you take him back?</i>

339
00:21:42,109 --> 00:21:43,629
<i>He's never suffered much.</i>

340
00:21:43,629 --> 00:21:45,389
<i>It's tiring to work in a hotpot restaurant.</i>

341
00:21:45,389 --> 00:21:47,630
<i>I'm not taking him with me.</i>

342
00:21:48,360 --> 00:21:49,900
<i>Do me a favor.</i>

343
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:51,299
<i>Get him a job.</i>

344
00:21:51,299 --> 00:21:52,589
<i>Keep an eye on him.</i>

345
00:21:52,589 --> 00:21:56,090
<i>- Every night, report his work performance to me by phone.
- Huh?</i>

346
00:21:56,090 --> 00:21:57,250
<i>Why are you whining?</i>

347
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:59,589
<i>You're making me betray my friend.</i>

348
00:21:59,589 --> 00:22:01,640
<i>I'm not such a man.</i>

349
00:22:05,530 --> 00:22:08,410
<i>Will you betray him</i>

350
00:22:08,410 --> 00:22:10,910
<i>or betray me?</i>

351
00:22:10,910 --> 00:22:13,080
<i>Make a choice.</i>

352
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:21,160
<i>I'll betray him.</i>

353
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:23,260
<i>That's more like it.</i>

354
00:22:23,260 --> 00:22:25,019
<i>Anyway, this isn't a betrayal.</i>

355
00:22:25,019 --> 00:22:27,200
<i>I'm doing this for his benefit.</i>

356
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:30,670
<i>Brother Liang!</i>

357
00:22:30,670 --> 00:22:32,259
<i>Why does he shit so quickly?</i>

358
00:22:32,259 --> 00:22:33,949
<i>He has a good digestive system. Go back.</i>

359
00:22:33,949 --> 00:22:35,560
<i>Hold on.</i>

360
00:22:45,740 --> 00:22:47,540
<i>Brother Liang!</i>

361
00:22:49,220 --> 00:22:51,220
<i>Brother Liang!</i>

362
00:22:51,220 --> 00:22:52,900
<i>Take it.</i>

363
00:22:53,700 --> 00:22:55,430
<i>Treat yourself to something nice.</i>

364
00:22:55,430 --> 00:22:56,850
<i>Don't buy cigarettes.</i>

365
00:22:56,850 --> 00:22:58,610
<i>Thank you, Brother.</i>

366
00:22:58,610 --> 00:23:00,730
<i>I'll get going.</i>

367
00:23:02,770 --> 00:23:04,970
<i>Brother Liang! Brother Liang!</i>

368
00:23:04,970 --> 00:23:07,180
<i>Brother Liang, why did you wander so far away?</i>

369
00:23:07,180 --> 00:23:09,590
<i>It stinks like hell there.</i>

370
00:23:09,590 --> 00:23:11,699
<i>I ate too much.</i>

371
00:23:11,699 --> 00:23:13,989
<i>- Let's go back.</i>
<i>- Okay.</i>

372
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:21,600
You even had him on GPS tracking?

373
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:23,600
I don't have to do that.

374
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:25,400
He's using my old phone.

375
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:27,000
All the accounts on it are mine.

376
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,600
He's too uneducated to know about such things.

377
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:31,600
That's the same as GPS tracking.

378
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:34,800
My dad left him here, and he's like a wild horse.

379
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:38,000
I can't keep an eye on him without modern technology.

380
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,200
Well, why didn't you say a word?

381
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:41,400
You're the talk of the village.

382
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:43,200
You can't keep secrets in the village.

383
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:46,000
I have to keep my mouth shut if I don't want others to know.

384
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,400
Besides, he has his own informant.

385
00:23:47,400 --> 00:23:50,400
Xia Xia pouts his chin whenever he lies.

386
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:52,500
"Brother, I know nothing."

387
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:54,600
It's obvious that he's lying.

388
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,900
You can't even tell me, right?

389
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:03,600
You're the number one suspect in leaking secrets.

390
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,600
I didn't even tell Granny.

391
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:07,800
However, I told Aunty Feng.

392
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:09,800
She's tight-lipped.

393
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:12,900
He told me he found A'Yuan, but he's conducting reform through labor.

394
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:15,800
He told me not to worry.

395
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:19,200
Look. That's why I don't wany Granny intervening.

396
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:21,200
If Granny were 20 years old,

397
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:23,600
she could win the Women's Chinese Kickboxing Championship.

398
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,599
I'll tell you this. When Grandpa was younger,

399
00:24:26,599 --> 00:24:29,079
Granny nabbed him for his great singing voice.

400
00:24:29,080 --> 00:24:31,079
- She nabbed him and brought him home?
- Yes.

401
00:24:31,079 --> 00:24:33,000
My grandpa was a popular lad.

402
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:35,800
Granny might not have gorgeous looks,

403
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:38,200
but she was a robust woman.

404
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,800
Do you think I can't beat you up?

405
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:43,000
Yes, you're pretty. You're the most beautiful.

406
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,800
Don't listen to his nonsense.

407
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:46,700
He must be talking rubbish.

408
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:50,000
I bet you were a gorgeous young lady.

409
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:52,500
You're the gorgeous one.

410
00:24:52,500 --> 00:24:54,400
Stop flattering each other.

411
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:55,800
Flattering?

412
00:24:56,500 --> 00:24:58,400
Everything he says sounds so foul.

413
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:00,600
Yeah, this isn't flattery.

414
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:04,800
This is mutual appreciation between women.

415
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:08,400
Ignore him. Let's eat.

416
00:25:09,500 --> 00:25:12,000
Oh, let's take a photo as a keepsake.

417
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:17,400
Come on. Chairman Xie.

418
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:20,000
Granny, look over here.

419
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,600
A peace sign is so corny.

420
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:22,800
Here's a heart.

421
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:24,600
A heart is corny.

422
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:31,000
Did I close my eyes?

423
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:33,400
It's pretty nice.

424
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:35,200
Let me see.

425
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,400
Have some more food.

426
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:43,000
Granny, you're giving her all the meat. I just put them in.

427
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:45,000
You can just add more.

428
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:46,900
That's enough. Eat more.

429
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:48,200
Thank you.

430
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,600
That's all.

431
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:13,700
Say something.

432
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:15,600
What am I supposed to say?

433
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:18,100
You can scold me if you want to. Don't hold it in.

434
00:26:18,100 --> 00:26:21,000
I've never restrained myself from scolding you.

435
00:26:24,400 --> 00:26:26,200
How about this?

436
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:30,700
Keep this a secret from Mom at all costs.

437
00:26:30,700 --> 00:26:32,400
She's so frugal.

438
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:36,600
Even a few cents for groceries matters so much to her.

439
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:39,700
If she finds out you were cheated of such a hefty sum, she'll keep silent

440
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:41,900
but toss and turn every night.

441
00:26:43,600 --> 00:26:45,000
As for money,

442
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:47,200
don't borrow from our brother.

443
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:51,200
I have some savings to make up for the ¥30,000.

444
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:55,100
It's best if we can recover the money from the phishing scam.

445
00:26:55,100 --> 00:26:58,800
Even if that money is lost, wipe it from your mind.

446
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:02,000
Take this as a lesson learned. Leave this matter in the past.

447
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:05,600
Brother won't mention a word about this.

448
00:27:05,600 --> 00:27:07,800
None of us should mention it either.

449
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:10,400
Why are you staring at me?

450
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:12,400
Aren't you going to scold me?

451
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:15,200
I've scolded you loads! You just don't listen to a word I say.

452
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:18,500
You should know your own intellect.

453
00:27:18,500 --> 00:27:21,400
They stopped you from telling your family to avoid being seen through.

454
00:27:21,400 --> 00:27:24,000
Do you really think it's that easy to earn money?

455
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:25,300
I have another question for you.

456
00:27:25,300 --> 00:27:27,800
Have Mom and I ever asked you for a single cent?

457
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:29,300
Why are you so desperate?

458
00:27:29,300 --> 00:27:32,400
Is the world out there so rosy? Is staying at home so terrible?

459
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:37,200
Do you think I'm snapping at you again?

460
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:41,600
I don't hate staying at home.

461
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:45,400
I just want to make more money.

462
00:27:46,200 --> 00:27:48,800
The wood carving workshop doesn't profit much.

463
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:51,000
One person makes a huge difference.

464
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:53,800
Master can pay less minimum wage.

465
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:56,800
Brother came back to start a business.

466
00:27:56,800 --> 00:28:00,200
You quit your job in Kunming and came home.

467
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:03,000
In the past few years, he invested a lot of money here.

468
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:06,200
He hires so many people and distributes tons of wages.

469
00:28:06,200 --> 00:28:08,200
Yet, there are so few tourists.

470
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:14,600
Selling produce online only makes a small profit. He's barely making ends meet.

471
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:17,200
You can't get any bonuses either.

472
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:19,600
Why are you worrying about this?

473
00:28:19,600 --> 00:28:22,200
I'm the only man in the family, aren't I?

474
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:24,800
I should support the family in the future.

475
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:27,000
We can't just rely on you.

476
00:28:37,600 --> 00:28:41,400
Do you think I'm dumb for thinking too much?

477
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:47,800
- I know I'm stupid.
- You are stupid.

478
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:51,500
Do you know what it means

479
00:28:51,500 --> 00:28:53,800
to wear one's learning lightly?

480
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:56,000
How about the saying, "Success follows when the time is ripe"?

481
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:58,800
If there's water in a river, we have to start by digging ditches.

482
00:28:58,800 --> 00:29:01,600
Only then can the water be drawn to the ground.

483
00:29:01,600 --> 00:29:04,200
Many things need to be done step-by-step.

484
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:05,900
Haste won't get us anywhere.

485
00:29:05,900 --> 00:29:09,700
Mrs. Huailan has been an embroiderer all her life.

486
00:29:09,700 --> 00:29:11,400
Right now, everyone treats her with respect

487
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:14,800
and calls her Master Xie.

488
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:19,700
When you were learning wood carving from your master,

489
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:21,600
you studied during the day and practiced at night.

490
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:24,800
You put in so much effort for so many years.

491
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:28,000
You finally carved a worthless old wooden basin

492
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:30,200
into a piece of handicraft and sold it.

493
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:34,400
Oftentimes, you can't focus on immediate gratification.

494
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:36,300
It takes time to develop,

495
00:29:36,300 --> 00:29:38,000
but that's not necessarily obvious to the eye.

496
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:41,600
You're always so impatient. Well, doesn't that make you a fool?

497
00:29:41,600 --> 00:29:44,200
Master hasn't even earned much after a lifetime of work.

498
00:29:44,200 --> 00:29:48,400
Tell me. How much is a windfall?

499
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:54,400
Your master keeps his family fed with his own skills.

500
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:56,800
He also passes these skills on

501
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:59,500
so that his apprentices can also support their own families.

502
00:29:59,500 --> 00:30:01,400
Isn't that enough?

503
00:30:03,600 --> 00:30:07,500
- The internet said—
- Stop listening to the ramblings of others.

504
00:30:07,500 --> 00:30:10,100
Can't you think for yourself?

505
00:30:10,100 --> 00:30:13,000
I can only say the same thing. Do you think it's that easy to earn money?

506
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:15,000
When encountering problems,

507
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:17,600
we should think about how to sell our best items.

508
00:30:17,600 --> 00:30:18,800
All you do is flee.

509
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:21,500
Xie Xiaoxia, listen up. Do you know what we call your behavior?

510
00:30:21,500 --> 00:30:24,000
Gluttonous, lazy, overambitious, and indolent.

511
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:26,600
You'll be a failure in life.

512
00:30:28,100 --> 00:30:30,000
Fine, I'll stop my nagging.

513
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:32,000
Contemplate on your own.

514
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:37,600
I got it.

515
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:39,200
You got it?

516
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,600
Can I have a taste?

517
00:30:45,600 --> 00:30:48,600
Of course. It's homemade. Have a taste.

518
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:50,400
Here you go.

519
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:55,100
- Try it.
- Thank you.

520
00:30:56,800 --> 00:30:58,000
How much are they?

521
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:00,400
